title Collaboration Diagram: Complete System Interactions

' --- THE HUMAN ACTORS ---
actor \"Admin\" as Admin
actor \"Driver\" as Driver
actor \"Passenger\" as Pass

' --- THE APPS (YOUR CODE) ---
rectangle \"Admin Portal\" as AdminApp
rectangle \"Driver PWA\" as DriverApp
rectangle \"Passenger PWA\" as PassApp

' --- THE BACKEND (YOUR INFRASTRUCTURE) ---
component \"Firebase Cloud\" as Firebase

' --- THE VISUALIZATION (EXTERNAL) ---
component \"Google Maps API\" as Google

' --- ALIGNMENT (FORCE GRID) ---
Driver -[hidden]right- Admin
Admin -[hidden]right- Pass

DriverApp -[hidden]right- AdminApp
AdminApp -[hidden]right- PassApp

' Force Google Maps to sit separately at the bottom right
Firebase -[hidden]right- Google

' --- INTERACTIONS ---

' 1. DRIVER FLOW (Generates Data)
Driver -down-> DriverApp : \"1. Start Trip\"
DriverApp -down-> Firebase : \"2. Upload Stream\"

' 2. ADMIN FLOW (Manages Data)
Admin -down-> AdminApp : \"3. Login\"
AdminApp -down-> Firebase : \"4. Update Fleet\"

' 3. PASSENGER FLOW (Reads Data)
Pass -down-> PassApp : \"5. Open Map\"
PassApp -down-> Firebase : \"6. Subscribe\"
Firebase -up-> PassApp : \"7. Push Update\"

' 4. VISUALIZATION FLOW (The 'Why')
' Both apps ask Google to paint the screen
DriverApp -down-> Google : \"8. Render Nav\"
PassApp -down-> Google : \"9. Render Tiles\"
